=== 法拉利的绰号 ===
恩佐·法拉利有多个绰号：<ref name="ReferenceA" /><ref>Oscar Orefici, ''Ferrari: romanzo di una vita'', Cairo, Milano, 2007.</ref>
*{{lang|it|"Il Commendatore"}}（“团长”），来自他获得的{{link-en|意大利王冠勋章|Order of the Crown of Italy|三级王冠勋章}}({{lang|it|'''Commendatore''' dell'Ordine della Corona}})，是法拉利最广为人知的绰号之一。这一绰号有时会被不知道来由的外国人理解为英语的{{lang|en|"the Commander"}}（“指挥官”）。法拉利自己不喜欢{{lang|it|Il Commendatore}}的绰号，因为他的王冠勋章是法西斯政权颁发的，且在二战后已被废止（见上文）。<ref name="Memoir" /><ref name="aLife">{{Cite book |url=https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/1004571338 |title=Enzo Ferrari : a life |last=Richard |first=Williams |publisher=2011 |isbn=978-1-4464-5037-6 |location=London |oclc=1004571338 |quote=Italians are fond of titles, yet they meant little to him, or at least only in one specific sense. Between the wars he was made first a Cavaliere and then a Commendatore, the rough equivalents of a knighthood or a Légion d'honneur. He had no use for them. Anyway he always said that Commendatore was a Fascist title. He preferred to be addressed as Ingegnere ....}}</ref>
*{{lang|it|"Il Cavaliere"}}(“骑士”)，来自他获得的{{link-en|劳动功绩勋章|Order of Merit for Labour|劳动功绩勋章}}({{lang|it|'''Cavaliere''' del lavoro}})
*{{lang|it|"Il Grande Vecchio"}}（“老爷子”）
*{{lang|it|"Il Drake"}}(“德雷克”)，源自英国著名的[[私掠船长|私掠船长]][[弗朗西斯·德雷克|弗朗西斯·德雷克]]，是法拉利的英国对手起的绰号。这一绰号源自法拉利领导的小公司能够取得远超自己体量的胜利，法拉利自身独裁式的管理方式，以及他偶尔试探规则界限的行为。
*{{lang|it|"L'Ingegnere"}}（“工程师”）<ref>须注意的是在意大利，使用"Ingegnere"这一头衔要求必须拥有相关学位，或是通过相关的资格考试后经注册批准。法拉利因具有博洛尼亚大学机械工程系荣誉学位，因而具有这一资格。参见[http://www.cni-online.it/Home/Details/3264] {{Wayback|url=http://www.cni-online.it/Home/Details/3264 |date=20210311014205 }}</ref>
恩佐·法拉利相对更喜欢{{lang|it|"L'Ingegnere"}}的绰号，但更喜欢直接被叫做“法拉利”。<ref name="Memoir" /><ref name="aLife" />

=== 其他 ===
[[File:Enzoferrari-signature-la_mia_fedeltà_al_viola.svg|thumb]]
* 法拉利一直用紫罗兰色的墨水签署文件。据他说选择紫色墨水是因为在自己的记忆中，父亲阿尔弗雷德写信后会使用一种油印装置把信复印下来，复印后的原本和复印本都会变成深紫色。<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.museocasaenzoferrari.it/il-mito-enzo-ferrari/il-colore-viola/ |title=Il Colore Viola |accessdate=2018-10-19 |author=Museo Casa Enzo Ferrari – Modena |language=it |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140728191208/http://www.museocasaenzoferrari.it/il-mito-enzo-ferrari/il-colore-viola/ |archivedate=2014-07-28 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

* 1950年代曾有记者问起恩佐·法拉利的私家车是不是法拉利汽车，对此法拉利回答“不是，我买不起。”<ref>Gianni Rogliatti, ''Sicilia: Targa Florio 1920'', [[L'Automobile|L'Automobile]], n.139 del 1979, pag.16</ref>
* 恩佐·法拉利生前坚决反对烟草广告的赞助，曾声称“我的车不吸烟”。<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.liberation.fr/sports/1997/03/08/une-saison-avec-ferrari-cinquantenairemes-voitures-ne-fumeront-jamais_200418 |title=Une saison avec Ferrari, cinquantenaire«Mes voitures ne fumeront jamais...» |newspaper=Libération.fr |accessdate=2018-10-19 |language=fr |archive-date=2020-09-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200919233247/https://www.liberation.fr/sports/1997/03/08/une-saison-avec-ferrari-cinquantenairemes-voitures-ne-fumeront-jamais_200418 |dead-url=no }}</ref>然而在法拉利过世后，烟草巨头[[菲利普莫里斯国际|菲利普莫里斯国际]]于1996年与法拉利车队达成赞助协议，旗下的[[万宝路|万宝路]]直到2011年都是法拉利车队的冠名赞助商。<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://formula-one.speedtv.com/article/f1-ferrari-drops-marlboro-from-team-name/ |title=F1: Ferrari Drops Marlboro From Team Name |author=Adam Cooper |date=2011-07-08 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130301211309/http://formula-one.speedtv.com/article/f1-ferrari-drops-marlboro-from-team-name/ |archivedate=2013-03-01}}</ref>
* 尽管自家汽车与车队的标志来自王牌飞行员的徽章，恩佐·法拉利一生从未搭乘过飞机。此外他还反感火车，甚至不肯使用[[电梯|电梯]]。<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.repubblica.it/motori/sezioni/attualita/2014/09/10/news/ferrari_alle_origini_del_mito-95400765/ |title=Ferrari, dalle origini del mito alla Borsa |date=2014-09-10 |newspaper=Repubblica.it |accessdate=2018-10-19 |language=it |archive-date=2019-12-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191228043314/https://www.repubblica.it/motori/sezioni/attualita/2014/09/10/news/ferrari_alle_origini_del_mito-95400765/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>
* 法拉利与著名男高音[[帕瓦罗蒂|帕瓦罗蒂]]既是同乡也是好友。<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/g2/story/0,,628610,00.html |title=It ain't over till the fat man stops singing |accessdate=2018-10-22 |work=www.theguardian.com |language=en |archive-date=2018-10-22 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181022232522/https://www.theguardian.com/g2/story/0,,628610,00.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>

